  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Capnography provides noninvasive monitoring of ventilation and can allow early recognition of
      altered respiration patterns and apnea. The aim of this prospective study was to compare the
      detection of apnea and the prediction of oxygen desaturation and hypoxemia by capnography
      versus clinical surveillance during procedural sedation for percutaneous transhepatic
      cholangiodrainage (PTCD).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
